### Vectorless RAG API — example requests
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client extension and JetBrains HTTP Client.
###
### Replace {{BASE_URL}} with your actual API Gateway URL, e.g.:
###   https://abc123def4.execute-api.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/prod
###
### You can also export it as a shell variable and use the curl equivalents below.

@BASE_URL = https://YOUR_API_ID.execute-api.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/prod

# ===========================================================================
# 1. Trigger ingestion of an already-uploaded S3 document
# ===========================================================================

### Ingest a PDF (custom doc_id)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/ingest
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "s3_key": "documents/annual-report-2024.pdf",
  "doc_id": "annual-report-2024"
}

###

### Ingest a Markdown file (auto-generated doc_id)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/ingest
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "s3_key": "documents/product-spec.md"
}

###

# ===========================================================================
# 2. Query an indexed document
# ===========================================================================

### Simple factual question
POST {{BASE_URL}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doc_id": "annual-report-2024",
  "question": "What was the total revenue for the year?"
}

###

### Multi-hop / summary question
POST {{BASE_URL}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doc_id": "annual-report-2024",
  "question": "What are the main strategic initiatives discussed in this report?"
}

###

### Specific detail lookup
POST {{BASE_URL}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doc_id": "annual-report-2024",
  "question": "Who is the CEO and what did they say about future growth?"
}

###

### Question not answerable from the document
POST {{BASE_URL}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doc_id": "annual-report-2024",
  "question": "What is the weather forecast for tomorrow?"
}

###


# ===========================================================================
# Curl equivalents
# ===========================================================================
#
# Export the base URL first:
#   export API_URL="https://YOUR_API_ID.execute-api.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/prod"
#
# --- Upload document ---
#   aws s3 cp ./my-document.pdf s3://YOUR_BUCKET_NAME/documents/my-document.pdf
#
# --- Ingest ---
#   curl -s -X POST "$API_URL/ingest" \
#     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#     -d '{"s3_key": "documents/my-document.pdf", "doc_id": "my-doc"}' | jq .
#
# --- Query ---
#   curl -s -X POST "$API_URL/query" \
#     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#     -d '{"doc_id": "my-doc", "question": "What are the key findings?"}' | jq .
#
# --- View Lambda logs (ingest) ---
#   aws logs tail /aws/lambda/vectorless-rag-ingest --follow
#
# --- View Lambda logs (query) ---
#   aws logs tail /aws/lambda/vectorless-rag-query --follow
